festival.introText:
Lets Rock Shrewsbury will take place at The Quarry on Saturday 15th July 2023. With a fabulous line-up of artists to bring you the very best of the 80s, and an action packed day of general 80s madness, there is plenty to do for everyone at this Family Friendly Festival!

Lets Rock has been leading the way for quality, family-friendly 80s music festivals since 2009. Don’t miss out on this chance for a retro blast with the very best of the 80s!
festival.festivalName: Lets Rock Shrewsbury - The Retro Festival

reviews.title: Review of Let\'s Rock Shrewsbury!
reviews.body: Venus was ok, sound on a few of the acts was rubbish, especially ABC who I waited all day to see. The prices were extortionate inside, 22 for a jug of Pimms that had very little Pimms in it

reviews.title: Review of Let\'s Rock Shrewsbury!
reviews.body: The whole day was awesome. Myself and my hubby really enjoyed it. He bought me tick*ts for my birthday as i had been bugging him for years to see Billy Ocean and this was the perfect opportunity to see him and lots of other 80's artists that we couldn't see back in the day. He especially wanted to see T'pau and ABC.  When we arrived at the venue there was a search of our bags which i was glad of considering what was going on with the terrorist threat and with the armed police on patrol we felt very safe. We bought a drink then went o find ourselves a spot to enjoy the entertainment. We managed to get right to the front which i was very happy about. I liked the fact that you could buy a wristband and raffle tick*ts which went to charity. The toilets were kept fairly clean most of the day with the amount of people that were using them. The only thing that was a bit bad was the size of the bar, it could have been bigger. I went to the bar to get a drink and missed the whole set of altered images as i was in the queue. Other than that it was the best birthday present ever. Oh one thing i would like to ask is would there be a digital copy of the show available to buy as i would love that, the money off them could also go to the charity, you could offer this to the people that attended the concert via there email as you sent this review request.

faqs.question: When is Lets Rock Shrewsbury 2023?
faqs.answer: Lets Rock Shrewsbury takes place on Saturday 15th July 2023.

faqs.question: What's included in a Lets Rock Shrewsbury VIP ticket?
faqs.answer:
2023 will see the ever popular and totally cool, funky 80s themed CLUB TROPICANA VIP enclosure.

 

As well as entry to the event, VIP tickets include fast track entry, luxury loos, meal and welcome drink, PLUS exclusive DJ sets.

 

Sit back and relax in this exclusive area with comfy seating and chairs and a full bar serving quality brands and 80’s cocktails, plus of course the all-important VIP luxury loos – essential at any festival!

 

Fancy dress is recommended, but not compulsory!

 

For any group or company bookings (10 or more) please email uklcs@uk-live.co.uk

faqs.question: How do I apply for a personal assistant ticket?
faqs.answer:
Disabled ticket holders are offered, subject to availability, a free ticket for a personal assistant.

 

This offer is open to those who hold a current higher rate of DLA or other UK government approved supporting evidence of their requirement for a personal assistant.

 

Carer tickets can only be issued against general entry tickets.

 

IMPORTANT: This offer is only available to those people that would be unable to attend the festival without a full time assistant. Every application is looked at on an individual basis and if anyone is found to be making a fraudulent application, the festival reserve the right to cancel both the original ticket and personal assistant ticket, before and during the event.

 

To apply for a personal assistant ticket, please follow the procedure below:

– Buy a standard general admission ticket (must be online)

– Email proof of purchase (the email from Gigantic) AND a copy of your letter of award for DLA (or equivalent)

 

Please send your email to uklcs@uk-live.co.uk .

 

Please ensure that any attachments do not exceed a file size of 1MB, and that you include your full postal address in your email.

 

PERSONAL ASSISTANT TICKETS WILL BE EMAILED ONE WEEK BEFORE THE EVENT

faqs.question: Does Lets Rock Shrewsbury have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Let's Rock Shrewsbury is a non-camping festival so camping equipment is not needed.

faqs.question: Where is Lets Rock Shrewsbury?
faqs.answer: Lets Rock Shrewsbury will be held at The Quarry, Shrewsbury.

faqs.question: What time does the event start/finish?
faqs.answer:
The gates open at 11.00am and we recommend that you get there early, so that you don’t miss any of the action!

 

The Festival starts at midday and finishes at 10:30pm.

faqs.question: Does Lets Rock Shrewsbury have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: No, Lets Rock Scotland is a family-friendly festival.

faqs.question: Will I be able to come and go during the day?
faqs.answer:
This is a no re-entry event. Re-entry to the Festival is not permitted, with the sole exception of parents/guardians accompanying children under the age of 16.

 

Single use re-entry wristbands will only be issued on-site at the Festival to parents/guardians who are in possession of a Child Ticket and this pass allows for re-entry to the festival with or without your child.

 

Adults not accompanying children to the Festival will not be allowed re-entry. Single use re-entry wristbands will also be available for disabled guests.
